{"title_page": "L\u00fctfullah Kayalar", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n | honorific-prefix   = \n | name               = L\u00fctfullah Kayalar\n | native_name        = <!--The person's name in their own language, if different.-->\n | native_name_lang   = <!--ISO 639-1 code, e.g., \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} in |native_name= instead.-->\n | honorific-suffix   = \n | image              = Lutfullah-kayalar-fotografi.jpg\n | image_size         = \n | smallimage         = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n | alt                = \n | caption            = \n | order              = \n | office             = Minister of Finance of Turkey\n | term_start         = 6 March 1996\n | term_end           = 28 June 1996\n | predecessor        = [[\u0130smet Atilla]]\n | successor          = [[Abd\u00fcllatif \u015eener]]\n | office2             = Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Rural Affairs of Turkey\n | term_start2         = 31 March 1989\n | term_end2           = 23 June 1991\n | predecessor2        = [[H\u00fcsn\u00fc Do\u011fan]]\n | successor2          = [[\u0130lker Tuncay]]\n | birth_date         = 1952\n | birth_place        = [[Akda\u011fmadeni]], [[Yozgat]], [[Turkey]]\n}}\n'''L\u00fctfullah Kayalar''' (born 1952 in [[Yozgat]], [[Turkey]]) is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] lawyer from profession and politician, who served twice as government minister.\nHe graduated from the Law School of [[Ankara University]] with a [[Bachelor of Laws]] degree. He entered politics as a member of the [[Motherland Party (Turkey)|Motherland Party]], and was elected into the parliament as Deputy of Yozgat. L\u00fctfullah Kayalar served in the cabinet of [[Turgut \u00d6zal]] and later of [[Y\u0131ld\u0131r\u0131m Akbulut]] as Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Rural Affairs between 1989\u20131991,<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xntLAAAAYAAJ&q=%22L%C3%BCtfullah+Kayalar%22+-inpublisher:icon&dq=%22L%C3%BCtfullah+Kayalar%22+-inpublisher:icon&as_brr=0&hl=tr&cd=1 |publisher=Tar\u0131m Orman ve K\u00f6yi\u015fleri Bakanl\u0131\u01e7\u0131 |title=Zirai \u00d6\u011fretimin Y\u0131ld\u00f6n\u00fcm\u00fcn\u00fc Kutluyoruz- The Anniversary Of Agricultural Education |journal=Tar\u0131m Orman ve K\u00f6yi\u015fleri Bakanl\u0131\u01e7\u0131 Dergisi |issue=35 |volume=1989-01 |page=45 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2010-12-14 }}</ref> and in the cabinet of [[Mesut Y\u0131lmaz]] as Minister of Finance in 1996.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=goVpAAAAMAAJ&q=%22L%C3%BCtfullah+Kayalar%22+-inpublisher:icon&dq=%22L%C3%BCtfullah+Kayalar%22+-inpublisher:icon&as_brr=0&hl=tr&cd=4 |publisher=Do\u011fan Kitap |title=G\u00fcvercinli y\u0131llar |author=Tokatl\u0131, Orhan |year=2004 |pages=343 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2010-12-14 }}</ref>\n\nAt the Motherland Party's 7th congress held on August 4\u20135, 2001 in Ankara, he ran for the party leadership against Mesut Y\u0131lmaz, however without success.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://yenisafak.com.tr/arsiv/2001/agustos/05/politika.html |newspaper=[[Yeni \u015eafak]] |title=ANAP de\u011fi\u015fim istemedi |language=Turkish |date=2001-08-05 |accessdate=2010-12-14 }}</ref>\n \nBefore the [[2007 Turkish general election|2007 general election]], the two liberal parties, [[Democratic Party (Turkey, current)|Democratic Party]] and the Motherland Party, which he was a member of, wanted to merge in order to contest the elections as one party. However, as this intention failed, L\u00fctfullah Kayalar left his party and entered on June 2, 2007 the [[Republican People's Party (Turkey)|Republican People's Party]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sondakika/6640511.asp?gid=71 |newspaper=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |title=CHP Merkez Y\u00fcr\u00fctme Kurulu topland\u0131 |date=2007-06-03 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2010-12-14 }}</ref> a center-left party, accepting the invitation of its leader [[Deniz Baykal]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.todayszaman.com/newsDetail_getNewsById.action?load=detay&link=130192&bolum=103 |newspaper=[[Today's Zaman]] |title=Baykal leans to the right for CHP administration |author=Yavuz, Ercan |date=2007-12-27 |accessdate=2010-12-14 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/2007/06/27/yazar/tamer.html |newspaper=[[Milliyet]] |title=L\u00fctfullah Kayalar ile CHP se\u00e7im otob\u00fcs\u00fcnde... |author=Tamer, Meral |date=2007-06-27 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2010-12-14 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.habervitrini.com/haber.asp?id=283490 |publisher=Haber Vitrini |title=L\u00fctfullah Kayalar \u0130lk Kez Konu\u015ftu: ANAVATAN Ruhen ve Resmen Bitti, Art\u0131k CHP'liyim!.. |date=2007-06-17 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2010-12-14 }}</ref>\n\nHe is of [[Y\u00f6r\u00fcks|Y\u00f6ruk]] ancestry.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-off}}\n{{Succession box|\n  before= [[\u0130smet Attila]]|\n  title=[[List of Finance Ministers of Turkey|Minister of Finance of Turkey]] |\n  years=March 6, 1996&ndash;June 28, 1996 |\n  after=[[Abd\u00fcllatif \u015eener]]\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Ministers of Finance of Turkey}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kayalar, Lutfullah}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:People from Yozgat]]\n[[Category:Ankara University Faculty of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ministers of Finance of Turkey]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Turkey]]\n[[Category:Motherland Party (Turkey) politicians]]\n[[Category:Republican People's Party (Turkey) politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the 21st Parliament of Turkey]]\n[[Category:Members of the 20th Parliament of Turkey]]\n[[Category:20th-century Turkish lawyers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Turkish lawyers]]\n\n\n{{Turkey-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n | honorific-prefix   = \n | name               = L\u00fctfullah Kayalar\n | native_name        = <!--The person's name in their own language, if different.-->\n | native_name_lang   = <!--ISO 639-1 code, e.g., \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} in |native_name= instead.-->\n | honorific-suffix   = \n | image              = Lutfullah-kayalar-fotografi.jpg\n | image_size         = \n | smallimage         = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n | alt                = \n | caption            = \n | order              = \n | office             = Minister of Finance of Turkey\n | term_start         = 6 March 1996\n | term_end           = 28 June 1996\n | predecessor        = [[\u0130smet Atilla]]\n | successor          = [[Abd\u00fcllatif \u015eener]]\n | office2             = Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Rural Affairs of Turkey\n | term_start2         = 31 March 1989\n | term_end2           = 23 June 1991\n | predecessor2        = [[H\u00fcsn\u00fc Do\u011fan]]\n | successor2          = [[\u0130lker Tuncay]]\n | birth_date         = 1952\n | birth_place        = [[Akda\u011fmadeni]], [[Yozgat]], [[Turkey]]\n}}\n'''L\u00fctfullah Kayalar''' (born 1952 in [[Yozgat]], [[Turkey]]) is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] lawyer from profession and politician, who served twice as government minister.\nHe graduated from the Law School of [[Ankara University]] with a [[Bachelor of Laws]] degree. He entered politics as a member of the [[Motherland Party (Turkey)|Motherland Party]], and was elected into the parliament as Deputy of Yozgat. L\u00fctfullah Kayalar served in the cabinet of [[Turgut \u00d6zal]] and later of [[Y\u0131ld\u0131r\u0131m Akbulut]] as Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Rural Affairs between 1989-1991,<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xntLAAAAYAAJ&q=%22L%C3%BCtfullah+Kayalar%22+-inpublisher:icon&dq=%22L%C3%BCtfullah+Kayalar%22+-inpublisher:icon&as_brr=0&hl=tr&cd=1 |publisher=Tar\u0131m Orman ve K\u00f6yi\u015fleri Bakanl\u0131\u01e7\u0131 |title=Zirai \u00d6\u011fretimin Y\u0131ld\u00f6n\u00fcm\u00fcn\u00fc Kutluyoruz- The Anniversary Of Agricultural Education |journal=Tar\